# Trim the `railway up` upload to what the API Docker build consumes.
# The web package ballooned with committed splat assets (~hundreds of MB),
# which pushed the upload past the CLI's timeout. The Docker build needs
# every workspace member's package.json (frozen install) but only the
# types/api/foundry sources.
.git/
docs/
state/
infra/
configs/
e2e/
.claude/
output/
packages/web/*
!packages/web/package.json
tools/capture-factory/*
!tools/capture-factory/package.json
tools/twin-forge/*
!tools/twin-forge/package.json
